Deployment and Usage Guide for URL Hashing System
Step 1: Prerequisites
Ensure you have the following installed on your machine:

Node.js: Download Node.js (Ensure you have Node.js v14 or later)
MongoDB: Download MongoDB (or use a cloud version like MongoDB Atlas)
Postman: Download Postman (for testing API endpoints)
Step 2: Project Setup
Clone the Project Repository

Clone the project repository from GitHub to your local machine:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/AvviCoder/URL-Hashing-System.git
Navigate to the Project Directory

Move into the project folder:

cd your-repo
Install Project Dependencies

Install all the required dependencies using npm:
npm install
Set Up Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the root directory and add the following environment variables:

PORT=4000
DB_URL= mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/URlstore

Step 3: Running the Application
Start the Application
Run the application using the following command:

nodemon server.js
The server will start, and you should see a message like:

The server is running on http://localhost:4000
The database is connected successfully

After following this much of the steps the Use postman to get the provided test cases assesed
